inorganically sort

00:19:39.930 --> 00:19:41.090
of pour users in.

00:19:41.090 --> 00:19:43.440
We want it to have a healthy
sort of trajectory.

00:19:43.440 --> 00:19:47.600
We think that growth
for its own sake--

00:19:47.600 --> 00:19:49.730
we're not just looking
for spikes.

00:19:49.730 --> 00:19:53.430
We're looking for sustained,
organic, viral, exponential

00:19:53.430 --> 00:19:55.590
growth, and that happens
over time.

00:19:55.590 --> 00:19:59.070
Now some of this, as I pointed
out, we've managed to compress

00:19:59.070 --> 00:20:00.820
seven years into 20 months.

00:20:00.820 --> 00:20:02.385
That's awesome.

00:20:02.385 --> 00:20:07.040
But things have to happen in a
sequential order and as we

00:20:07.040 --> 00:20:07.870
open up APIs--

00:20:07.870 --> 00:20:10.230
Vic's talked a lot about this--
we want to ensure the

00:20:10.230 --> 00:20:13.390
integrity of the system both
from a spam and abuse point,

00:20:13.390 --> 00:20:16.490
from making sure the content
reached the right users in the

00:20:16.490 --> 00:20:18.430
right moment in the right way.

00:20:18.430 --> 00:20:22.560
There's a lot of science behind
that and some of that

00:20:22.560 --> 00:20:24.920
has to be learned
in the field.

00:20:24.920 --> 00:20:28.340
And so we've continued to
introduce new APIs, new

00:20:28.340 --> 00:20:31.950
functionality, Google+ Sign In,
all of these things, in

00:20:31.950 --> 00:20:35.400
disciplined, thoughtful ways
that have not impeded but

00:20:35.400 --> 00:20:39.610
rather accreted value to our
growth trajectories and the

00:20:39.610 --> 00:20:40.770
value of the network.

00:20:40.770 --> 00:20:42.810
LOUIS GRAY: And I think there's
also three pieces we

00:20:42.810 --> 00:20:44.860
touched on a number of times in
the keynote, and touched on

00:20:44.860 --> 00:20:46.280
a little bit with
spam and abuse.

